# Sunrise Budget — Project Context

Next.js 16 budget app with end-to-end encryption. Tech: React 19, TypeScript, Zustand, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, react-hook-form, Zod, Vitest.

## Structure (DDD)

- `src/app/` — Routes; pages compose features, no business logic
- `src/features/` — Feature modules with DDD layers:
  - **domain/** — Pure business logic (entities, types, pure functions). No React, store, or I/O.
  - **infrastructure/** — External I/O (store, persistence, export/import).
  - **presentation/** — UI components and hooks.
- `src/lib/` — Cross-cutting utilities (crypto, constants, format, utils, debounce). Feature domain logic in `features/*/domain/`
- `src/hooks/` — Shared hooks (e.g. from shadcn). Feature hooks in `features/*/presentation/hooks/`
- State — `src/features/budget/infrastructure/store.ts`, `src/features/session/infrastructure/store.ts`
- `src/components/` — Shared UI only (ui/, theme-provider, ErrorBoundary)

## Conventions

- New constants/labels → `lib/constants.ts`
- Feature domain logic → `features/<name>/domain/`
- Feature UI → `features/<name>/presentation/` + export from `index.ts`

## Security

Budget data is encrypted. Never log plaintext or expose decrypted data in UI or error messages.
